<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3635] Allow setting arbitrary objects on PerfRunData</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3635</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;PerfRunData is used as the intermediary objects between PerfRunTasks. Just like we can set IndexReader/Writer on it, it will be good if it allows setting other arbitrary objects that are e.g. created by one task and used by another.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A recent example is the enhancement to the benchmark package following the addition of the facet module. We had to add TaxoReader/Writer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proposal is to add a HashMap&amp;lt;String, Object&amp;gt; that custom PerfTasks can set()/get(). I do not propose to move IR/IW/TR/TW etc. into that map. If however people think that we should, I can do that as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
